On 13.03.2026, Hon’ble Prime Minister Narendra Modi flagged off three new train services via video conferencing—Kamakhya–Charlapalli Amrit Bharat Express, Guwahati–New Jalpaiguri Express, and Narangi–Agartala Express—marking a significant step towards strengthening rail connectivity in the Northeast region.
On the same occasion, the Hon’ble Prime Minister also laid the foundation stone for the Wagon POH Workshop at Bashbari, which will further augment railway infrastructure and maintenance capacity in the region.
The flagging-off ceremony was attended by Hon’ble Minister Chandra Mohan Patowary, the Divisional Railway Manager/Lumding, other dignitaries, and a large gathering of members of the public.
The introduction of these new train services is expected to significantly enhance passenger convenience and improve regional connectivity.
